<br>
First, I think magicians should be the ultimate pet class. Most of our damage and abilities should revolve around our pet, after all we create him specifically to do our bidding. With that said, here are a few things I'd like to see.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Pet only weapons that are actually good.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
An upgrade to the &quot;runes&quot; line of weapons that would give +10 to all resists but be pet only. <br>
<br>
Bane weapons that are pet only, where the bane would actually stack above their damage. For instance a pet with a +5 bane vampire weapon would have 5 damage added to each hit against vampires, something like that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Pet only armor with stats that actually add to the pet's stats</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Armor with good resists but -hps<br>
<br>
Armor with +hps but -resists<br>
<br>
Armor with +dex +agi but -resists<br>
<br>
This would give us the ability to customize our pet for an encounter.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Pet &quot;lures&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
One or two pets that cast &quot;lure&quot; type spells that will actually land on higher level mobs. This pet would be very weak in hps to keep magicians from using it to solo things they aren't intended to, but strong on damage against higher level mobs to help mages in both groups and raids where our own nukes are heavily resisted and our normal pet's nukes do not work.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> More beneficial pet buffs</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The &quot;resist blah&quot; line of spells, pet only. Yes I know pets now go on our resists, but I'd rather be able to buff my pets resists independently of my own than have his resists match mine *shrug*<br>
<br>
Cure component added to pet heal. Doesn't make any sense that the master of pets can not cure his/her own pet.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Utility Pets</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
These pets would work like any other pet, which means we could not have another pet up and have any of the utility pets up.<br>
<br>
A pet at lvls 20, 39, and 54 that roots. Same cast time as the wizard basic root, same resist rate/length of hold. This pet would have approximately 10 hps at lvl 20, 45 hps at lvl 39, and 85 hps at lvl 54. This pet would disappear within 15 seconds after summoning if not directed to attack. This would give us the ability to walk through an area and maybe not have to gate if attacked. This pet would cast root immediately upon being sent at a mob.<br>
<br>
A pet that increases our mana regen. This pet would not attack a mob as normal if we were attacked.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> General things non pet related</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I think Phantasmal protection should be moved to lvl 49, and a second one given at 60 that gives us the same mana regen as clarity. Sorry, just bugs me that druids have better mana regen than us, and yes it is a jealousy thing lol<br>
<br>
Pets should be considered a part of the group when group spells are cast or group songs are sung. This has long been an annoyance of mine.<br>
<br>
/drop command. Come on, it can't be that hard to implement and it's silly that we spend so much of a raid with an inventory full of bandaids or else staring at the ceiling/floor.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying we should have all of these things, but perhaps some of them.<br>
<br>
<br>
